1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:01,510
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,510 --> 00:00:02,540
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:02,540 --> 00:00:03,540
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:03,810 --> 00:00:05,010
(Humangen Diagnostic Center)

5
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:06,610
(The results are indicative
of a paternal relationship.)

6
00:00:07,380 --> 00:00:08,380
What the...

7
00:00:09,180 --> 00:00:10,850
Park Hyun Jun is Song Geun Tae's...

8
00:00:13,050 --> 00:00:14,350
He's Driver Song's son?

9
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:17,520
(Bit Life President, Kim Myung Hui)

10
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:18,820
(Episode 70)

11
00:00:21,530 --> 00:00:23,860
(Humangen Diagnostic Center)

12
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:29,800
Choi Yu Na.

13
00:00:31,470 --> 00:00:32,470
(Suspicions Grow Over
CEO Baek Jun Gi's Death)

14
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,610
No!

15
00:00:35,610 --> 00:00:38,780
Files on CEO Baek's accident
from seven years ago.

16
00:00:39,680 --> 00:00:42,010
You were trying to hide this
in my mother's desk?

17
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:47,550
To frame my mother for investigating
CEO Baek Jun Gi's car accident?

18
00:00:47,990 --> 00:00:49,450
You thought
if my father pressured my mother,

19
00:00:50,090 --> 00:00:51,760
I would back off.

20
00:00:54,060 --> 00:00:56,330
Yes, I did.

21
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,930
Even when I begged you,
when I said I'd rather die,

22
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:00,970
you said you wouldn't stop.

23
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:04,140
You were determined to dig up
what happened seven years ago.

24
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:07,510
- I had to stop you.
- It's already too late.

25
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:10,140
I'm aware...

26
00:01:11,110 --> 00:01:13,750
of everything you did
seven years ago.

27
00:01:15,650 --> 00:01:16,650
What?

28
00:01:17,350 --> 00:01:19,920
You used Jin Ju
to lure out CEO Baek Jun Gi,

29
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:22,120
and when Jin Ju begged you for help,

30
00:01:23,020 --> 00:01:24,420
you threw a rock at her.

31
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:25,720
You...

32
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:27,530
How did you know about that?

33
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:32,100
You hurt Jin Ju, then went on
to win an award with her design?

34
00:01:33,030 --> 00:01:36,270
You stole Jin Ju's life.
Don't you feel any shame or guilt?

35
00:01:36,970 --> 00:01:37,970
I told you...

36
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,570
I'd make you pay
for what you did to her.

37
00:01:40,910 --> 00:01:42,940
Just you wait.

38
00:01:43,210 --> 00:01:46,380
I'm going to expose every
single evil thing you've done...

39
00:01:47,050 --> 00:01:50,150
and make sure you suffer for it.

40
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,330
What do I do?

41
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:04,300
How did Park Min Jun find out
about what happened back then?

42
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,770
What am I going to do?

43
00:02:08,330 --> 00:02:09,330
What do I do now?

44
00:02:11,370 --> 00:02:14,170
Please accept me as
the Adele family's daughter-in-law.

45
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:17,840
Let's be a family
and try to get along.

46
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:19,780
Father.

47
00:02:22,510 --> 00:02:23,520
And...

48
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:25,320
Lady Kim.

49
00:02:29,490 --> 00:02:30,590
Lady Kim?

50
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:35,930
You think you can force your way
into this family?

51
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:41,200
That's enough.
You two, go upstairs for now.

52
00:02:42,270 --> 00:02:43,270
Sir!

53
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,600
You said
you'd let me handle their matter.

54
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:49,770
Myung Hui,
I may have left it to you,

55
00:02:50,410 --> 00:02:54,010
but there can't be any issues
with the exclusive development rights.

56
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:55,950
They said there's a penalty fee,

57
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,720
so let's just think it over
for a few days.

58
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,420
- Thank you, Father.
- What...

59
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,990
We had to move in
to save our marriage,

60
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,690
but suddenly
sharing a room like this...

61
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:39,660
is a little awkward.

62
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:44,860
I'll be careful not to make
you uncomfortable.

63
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:47,330
No, that's not what I meant.

64
00:03:48,070 --> 00:03:49,630
I don't mind
being uncomfortable at all.

65
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:53,070
I'll sleep on the floor here,
so don't worry.

66
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:59,180
I'll never do anything
you don't want me to.

67
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,250
I know.

68
00:04:15,230 --> 00:04:17,130
(24H Movers)

69
00:04:20,970 --> 00:04:22,400
What is all this?

70
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:24,300
Well...

71
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:28,770
It's Chloe's things.

72
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:31,880
What?

73
00:04:32,210 --> 00:04:33,410
Since they're married,

74
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:36,510
she said she's moving in.

75
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:42,420
Min Jun.

76
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,870
We decided to start
living together today.

77
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:31,740
There were articles saying...

78
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:33,840
our marriage was fake
or that we'd broken up,

79
00:05:33,910 --> 00:05:35,940
so we had to rush things.

80
00:05:36,010 --> 00:05:38,310
If you want to blame someone,
blame your mother.

81
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:45,780
Min Jun.

82
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,190
Did we do something wrong?

83
00:05:55,490 --> 00:05:57,860
We're married
and want to live together.

84
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:00,000
Why is everyone making
such a big deal out of it?

85
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:01,100
Sure.

86
00:06:02,230 --> 00:06:05,540
Since you're married,
I guess you can live in the same house.

87
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,240
But if you think this marriage...

88
00:06:08,610 --> 00:06:11,110
will help you take over Adele,

89
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:13,310
you're fooling yourself,

90
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:15,180
and you've made a huge mistake.

91
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:22,090
Because Park Hyun Jun can never
be Adele Group's successor.

92
00:06:23,790 --> 00:06:26,620
President Kim,
even at a time like this,

93
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:28,590
you only care about Adele Group.

94
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:32,330
Aren't you being a little
too obvious about your greed?

95
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:39,070
That's rich,
coming from the person...

96
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:42,310
pretending to have amnesia
and putting on an act.

97
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,580
I mean, that's outright shameless.

98
00:07:15,970 --> 00:07:17,410
I guess...

99
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:20,480
I can't stop you
or hold on to you anymore, can I?

100
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:23,920
Is this the only way I can love you,

101
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:26,750
by quietly enduring it?

102
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:32,460
How did we end up like this?

103
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:36,330
Why? Darn it!

104
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:43,870
Right.

105
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:46,500
That's where it all went wrong.

106
00:07:47,370 --> 00:07:49,310
That day, seven years ago.

107
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,410
It all started with that accident.

108
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:01,050
You used Jin Ju
to lure out CEO Baek Jun Gi,

109
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:03,590
and when Jin Ju begged you for help,

110
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:05,490
you threw a rock at her.

111
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:06,690
Just you wait.

112
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:10,490
I'm going to expose every
single evil thing you've done...

113
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:13,900
and make sure you suffer for it.

114
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,540
The rock.

115
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:22,170
Only Baek Jin Ju and I
knew about that.

116
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:25,080
How could he have found out?

117
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:29,980
Don't tell me there was a witness.

118
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,590
I have to stop Park Min Jun.

119
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:43,160
(DNA Parentage Test Report)

120
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:45,160
(Subject 1: Park Hyun Jun,
Subject 2: Song Geun Tae)

121
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,870
Maybe I can use this.

122
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,240
I have to find a way somehow.

123
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:11,490
Why did your father...

124
00:09:12,790 --> 00:09:16,060
try to kill my dad and me?

125
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:22,470
Did stealing Temi Bio
to satisfy his greed...

126
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:24,940
make him happy?

127
00:09:30,310 --> 00:09:32,180
There's no way he was happy.

128
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:34,510
My family...

129
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:38,120
We all suspect one another,

130
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,150
hate one another,

131
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:43,150
and try to kill one another.

132
00:09:44,860 --> 00:09:46,220
It's not just my father.

133
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:49,260
No one will ever be happy.

134
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,870
Why are you asking that
all of a sudden?

135
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,340
I was just curious.

136
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:05,740
I'm hurting Min Jun...

137
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:08,950
and using you, Hyun Jun,
to take over Adele.

138
00:10:10,010 --> 00:10:14,250
Will I be happy
once I've gotten my revenge?

139
00:10:14,950 --> 00:10:16,190
I wonder.

140
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:21,760
I probably won't be happy either,
just like Chairman Park.

141
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:27,600
Still, I want to watch
Park Tae Ho crumble.

142
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:29,770
I'm going to see this through
to the end.

143
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:54,530
What the...

144
00:10:57,430 --> 00:10:58,430
What?

145
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:01,430
You startled me!

146
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:04,570
What was that for? Unbelievable.

147
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,340
Why am I here?

148
00:11:08,610 --> 00:11:11,280
What did you do to me?
What did you do?

149
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:13,640
You're the one
who caused a scene, you know.

150
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:16,350
You kept saying you couldn't leave
and that you had more questions.

151
00:11:16,580 --> 00:11:20,380
You insisted on coming to our place.
Seriously, you were such a pain.

152
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:25,590
And that's how you ended up
following us home and passing out...

153
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:26,760
in that state.

154
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:30,530
No, I wouldn't have...

155
00:11:30,530 --> 00:11:31,560
Whatever.

156
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,870
Eat before you leave
and sober up a bit.

157
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:01,590
This is the right way to eat it.

158
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:03,460
Go on, dig in.

159
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:07,000
Stop it right there.
What did you just do?

160
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:10,400
Putting kimchi on his rice
is crossing the line.

161
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:13,200
Crossing the line?

162
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:18,480
You're the one
who's crossing the line.

163
00:12:19,140 --> 00:12:21,380
"Even if you hate someone,
you still feed them well."

164
00:12:21,380 --> 00:12:23,210
That's our family motto.

165
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,820
I had to let him know
the kimchi is the main event.

166
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:28,920
Just shut it and sober up too.

167
00:12:29,690 --> 00:12:31,220
Dig in already.

168
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:34,690
Hurry up and eat.

169
00:12:35,660 --> 00:12:36,830
Right, sure.

170
00:12:37,530 --> 00:12:38,860
That I should.

171
00:12:42,370 --> 00:12:43,470
This turned out great.

172
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:47,040
- Hits the spot, right?
- Yes.

173
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,350
Is there anything you need?

174
00:12:58,620 --> 00:12:59,750
No.

175
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:03,820
I'd like to prepare
my mother-in-law's meals myself.

176
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:06,420
Here. I'll take that.

177
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:10,690
I appreciate the thought,
but this is my job.

178
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:15,330
Then at least let me help.

179
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:17,800
Oh my.

180
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:22,010
Oh, no. I'm so sorry.

181
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:25,080
See? I told you I should handle it.

182
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:28,210
I'll clean it up, so don't
touch anything. Just stay put.

183
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:33,550
- Good grief.
- Oh no.

184
00:13:35,620 --> 00:13:37,290
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Ok.

185
00:13:40,860 --> 00:13:41,860
Then...

186
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:45,460
Just unbelievable.

187
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:54,070
You call these side dishes?
There's no meat.

188
00:13:55,010 --> 00:13:57,210
If you don't want it,
then don't eat it.

189
00:13:57,410 --> 00:14:00,640
I have to go check
on the chairman's meal.

190
00:14:07,020 --> 00:14:08,020
You...

191
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:11,320
- How can you even eat right now?
- Come on.

192
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:14,430
You're not even supposed
to bother a dog when it's eating.

193
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:20,860
Wait, what's this?

194
00:14:22,370 --> 00:14:23,370
Jung Ran!

195
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,310
What is it?

196
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:33,410
I want to meet with you in person
to talk about Kim Dan Hui.

197
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:36,880
I'll be waiting outside
the main gate tomorrow at 9 a.m.

198
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:38,780
Outside the main gate?

199
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:41,190
She wants you to sneak out of here?

200
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:45,360
Apparently, Chloe's testing me.

201
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:48,530
She's practically challenging me
to escape.

202
00:14:48,590 --> 00:14:49,630
What?

203
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:51,860
I know you're clever,

204
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:53,500
but how are you going
to get out of here?

205
00:15:13,950 --> 00:15:18,260
Having breakfast together like this
really feels like we're a family.

206
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,160
It's finally sinking in...

207
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:22,660
that I'm part of the Adele family
and your daughter-in-law.

208
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:26,530
Since you've already accepted her,
please try to be more welcoming.

209
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:29,200
Be nice?

210
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,670
To the people
who followed Oh Jung Ran's orders...

211
00:15:31,970 --> 00:15:33,640
and tried to kill me?

212
00:15:33,940 --> 00:15:37,140
I want to kill Oh Jung Ran
this very minute,

213
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:40,880
but I'm holding back
because she begged me.

214
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:42,610
You don't know
what you're talking about.

215
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:46,150
As for you, the only reason
I'm seeing you again is because...

216
00:15:46,150 --> 00:15:47,550
of the exclusive development rights.

217
00:15:49,050 --> 00:15:50,150
Father.

218
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:53,020
If you can't see me as family,

219
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,990
you can see me
as a business partner.

220
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:58,930
As JKL Partners launches
this joint development project,

221
00:15:59,060 --> 00:16:01,830
we'd like Hyun Jun to head
the project for Adele.

222
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:05,200
The chairman is still recovering,

223
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:08,940
and he promised to make me
the acting chairman.

224
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:13,580
I plan to appoint someone
with expertise to lead the project.

225
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:17,780
But you don't hold
that position yet, do you?

226
00:16:18,850 --> 00:16:20,320
The chairman's decision
at this point...

227
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,220
can override
whatever you're planning.

228
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:27,360
Sir, please make your decision
right here and now.

229
00:16:27,860 --> 00:16:28,860
That's right.

230
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:31,560
Please firmly reject their proposal
right here and now.

231
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:46,880
Appoint Hyun Jun
to lead the project,

232
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:49,150
just as JKL Partners wants.

233
00:16:49,350 --> 00:16:50,450
Sir!

234
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:52,650
But in return,

235
00:16:54,450 --> 00:16:56,890
promote Min Jun to vice president...

236
00:16:57,150 --> 00:16:59,220
and put him on the successor track.

237
00:17:00,460 --> 00:17:02,490
I'll secure
the exclusive development rights...

238
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:05,930
while also looking out for my son.

239
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:27,990
Min Jun is now the vice president,

240
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:30,150
and he's on the successor track.

241
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:32,690
Don't even think about
getting in his way.

242
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,660
What do you think I can do?

243
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:37,260
Or maybe you're that insecure.

244
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:38,930
This is a warning.

245
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:41,730
Anyone who gets in Min Jun's way,

246
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:44,940
including Oh Jung Ran
and Park Hyun Jun,

247
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,900
will be forced out of Adele.

248
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:53,780
You could be the one
who gets swept out.

249
00:17:54,650 --> 00:17:58,220
After all, you're nobody
without the chairman.

250
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:11,630
Fine. Go on and be
as arrogant as you want.

251
00:18:12,860 --> 00:18:14,360
The greedier you become,

252
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:17,270
the more painful it'll be
when Hyun Jun's secret...

253
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,440
comes out.

254
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:26,910
Here's a change of clothes.

255
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:30,510
Where did you sleep?

256
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,520
Did you eat breakfast?

257
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:34,790
I took care of it.

258
00:18:35,690 --> 00:18:38,620
You're coming home today, right?

259
00:18:41,790 --> 00:18:44,460
Chloe and Hyun Jun
are already married,

260
00:18:44,860 --> 00:18:46,600
and Chloe has made up her mind.

261
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:50,470
I know it's hard, Min Jun,

262
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:52,900
but you need to move on.

263
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:57,910
I'd like to say I'll try.

264
00:18:58,910 --> 00:19:00,840
But honestly, I don't think I can.

265
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:04,150
Then at least throw yourself
into your work.

266
00:19:04,950 --> 00:19:07,280
You saw that you were appointed
vice president, right?

267
00:19:08,190 --> 00:19:09,190
Yes.

268
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:13,620
Chairman Park is leaning more
toward our side than theirs.

269
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:14,990
Take this chance...

270
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:18,760
and focus only on your goal
of taking over Adele Group.

271
00:19:19,860 --> 00:19:23,900
And for now,
leave the Temi Bio issue alone.

272
00:19:24,940 --> 00:19:27,100
It's just Temi Bio, right?

273
00:19:28,070 --> 00:19:30,870
There's another issue
I need to deal with anyway.

274
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:32,840
What other issue?

275
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,320
Director Park.

276
00:19:39,650 --> 00:19:41,180
I mean, Vice President Park.

277
00:19:41,390 --> 00:19:43,390
Will you be
at the company dinner today?

278
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:51,500
Thank you all for being here.

279
00:19:51,860 --> 00:19:53,430
I'm happy to have married Chloe...

280
00:19:53,430 --> 00:19:55,530
and to be starting
this joint venture.

281
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:57,670
It's my treat,
so please enjoy yourselves.

282
00:19:57,730 --> 00:19:59,300
Congratulations.

283
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,640
You two look great together.

284
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:04,240
Your marriage was the talk
of the office.

285
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,440
Congratulations.

286
00:20:05,510 --> 00:20:06,510
Thank you.

287
00:20:09,550 --> 00:20:12,420
It looks like everyone's here
for a company dinner.

288
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:15,250
Wait, aren't you the part-timer
from the cafe near our office?

289
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:17,320
Yes. I work part-time here too.

290
00:20:18,590 --> 00:20:20,590
I see the handsome director is here.

291
00:20:20,590 --> 00:20:22,190
Oh, right.

292
00:20:22,790 --> 00:20:23,790
It's been a while.

293
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:26,830
In that case,
I'll make yours extra delicious.

294
00:20:27,530 --> 00:20:29,430
When it comes to dakgalbi,
it's all about the hot plate.

295
00:20:29,630 --> 00:20:30,700
At our restaurant,

296
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:32,540
you get several different items
on one plate,

297
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:33,870
so it's fun to pick and choose.

298
00:20:33,870 --> 00:20:36,570
No way, look at this.
The cheese is the real deal.

299
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:41,210
Eating some makguksu in between
refreshes your palate,

300
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:42,880
so you can keep eating.

301
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:45,280
Chloe, try it like this.

302
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:53,260
I've never had
this combination before.

303
00:20:53,260 --> 00:20:54,660
It's unique and delicious.

304
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:57,590
Here, try some.

305
00:20:58,230 --> 00:21:00,300
The flying fish roe
gives it a real kick.

306
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:07,970
- It has a unique taste.
- Please enjoy.

307
00:21:15,950 --> 00:21:18,520
Yes, Manager Kang.
Has it been confirmed?

308
00:21:19,650 --> 00:21:23,690
Okay, then please take care of it
right away. I'm on my way now.

309
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,560
Everyone, enjoy your meal.

310
00:21:29,690 --> 00:21:32,630
Something's come up,
so I have to leave first.

311
00:21:33,430 --> 00:21:34,870
Sure thing.

312
00:21:54,790 --> 00:21:56,620
Where's Director Park Min Jun?

313
00:21:56,620 --> 00:21:59,820
He's Vice President Park now.

314
00:22:00,690 --> 00:22:03,090
By order of the vice president,
Ms. Choi Yu Na,

315
00:22:03,930 --> 00:22:05,260
your employment
is hereby terminated.

316
00:22:06,330 --> 00:22:09,430
Terminated?
What are you talking about?

317
00:22:10,030 --> 00:22:11,540
Seven years ago,

318
00:22:12,340 --> 00:22:15,040
you submitted a design
to the New Design Competition.

319
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:17,370
But it wasn't your work.

320
00:22:18,310 --> 00:22:20,580
I submitted the evidence...

321
00:22:21,010 --> 00:22:23,450
and had your award revoked.

322
00:22:23,450 --> 00:22:24,450
What?

323
00:22:25,050 --> 00:22:26,150
Park Min Jun, you...

324
00:22:26,150 --> 00:22:28,650
Your study-abroad scholarship
and job offer tied to your award...

325
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,420
have also been revoked.

326
00:22:30,490 --> 00:22:33,020
You'll have to return
the study-abroad funds,

327
00:22:33,090 --> 00:22:35,130
and I'm also filing a lawsuit
against you...

328
00:22:35,130 --> 00:22:36,530
for business interference,

329
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,500
- so prepare yourself.
- Is this really necessary?

330
00:22:40,130 --> 00:22:41,570
I'm just getting started.

331
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:45,900
I'll recover everything you stole
from Jin Ju,

332
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:47,670
down to the very last thing.

333
00:22:48,710 --> 00:22:49,870
Manager Kang,

334
00:22:50,310 --> 00:22:51,880
- drag her out of here.
- Yes, sir.

335
00:22:55,010 --> 00:22:56,310
Don't be ridiculous.

336
00:22:56,780 --> 00:23:00,780
Everything I have,
I earned through my own hard work.

337
00:23:01,620 --> 00:23:04,790
I'll be back.
I'll find a way to come back!

338
00:23:15,130 --> 00:23:16,930
Let me go.

339
00:23:20,470 --> 00:23:23,170
What's going on here?

340
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:25,310
It was discovered...

341
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,880
that Choi Yu Na stole
someone else's design...

342
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:30,280
seven years ago.

343
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:31,980
Her award has been revoked,

344
00:23:32,780 --> 00:23:34,250
and she's currently
being terminated.

345
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:38,790
Her award was revoked?

346
00:23:39,420 --> 00:23:41,020
I'm telling you, this is unfair.

347
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:45,130
Was this ordered by Park Min Jun?

348
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:47,900
Yes. It was
the first official order he gave...

349
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:49,770
after becoming vice president.

350
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:52,000
So that's why he left in a hurry.

351
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,370
In any case,

352
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:56,410
I'm glad this wrong
has finally been righted.

353
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,240
If you'll excuse me...

354
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:03,610
Seven years ago,

355
00:24:04,580 --> 00:24:06,550
you stole Baek Jin Ju's design.

356
00:24:06,850 --> 00:24:08,120
I reported it, too.

357
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,350
What?

358
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:11,350
You reported it seven years ago?

359
00:24:11,620 --> 00:24:12,620
Well,

360
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:16,730
I reported it
on Baek Jin Ju's behalf.

361
00:24:16,890 --> 00:24:21,300
The judging committee was supposed
to meet again for a review.

362
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:24,630
I guess we're finally seeing
the outcome now.

363
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:27,670
You're the one who reported it,

364
00:24:28,940 --> 00:24:30,240
not Baek Jin Ju?

365
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:37,350
Yu Na!

366
00:24:48,430 --> 00:24:49,760
Anyway, take care.

367
00:24:50,430 --> 00:24:54,200
Let's try not to see
each other again. Okay?

368
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:58,570
Let's go.

369
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:09,610
So it wasn't Baek Jin Ju.

370
00:25:11,210 --> 00:25:13,680
It was you, Park Hyun Jun?

371
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:23,530
My stomach!

372
00:25:23,530 --> 00:25:24,830
Jung Ran, are you okay?

373
00:25:25,030 --> 00:25:27,560
- Jung Ran, come on.
- What's wrong?

374
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:31,770
Mrs. Ok,
what did you put in our food?

375
00:25:32,300 --> 00:25:35,970
What the heck did you put in it
to make my stomach churn like this?

376
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:38,980
- My stomach!
- Hold on.

377
00:25:38,980 --> 00:25:40,510
I didn't put anything in it.

378
00:25:40,710 --> 00:25:44,580
Let me see. Where does it hurt?
How bad is it?

379
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:47,820
- Where?
- My stomach!

380
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,520
No!

381
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:52,960
Let go of me.

382
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:56,490
- My stomach!
- Let go of me. Stop.

383
00:25:57,790 --> 00:26:00,100
James asked about my past?

384
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:02,370
Exactly.

385
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:06,140
I was trying to see
if Chloe really lost her memory,

386
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:10,410
but he started asking
about your past, Dan Hui.

387
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:12,580
Why my past?

388
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,120
Yes, Mrs. Ok.

389
00:26:20,650 --> 00:26:23,190
What? Driver Song got out?

390
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,590
Yes, I hear you.

391
00:26:27,490 --> 00:26:28,930
I'll report this to Ms. Kim.

392
00:26:31,860 --> 00:26:34,660
Driver Song isn't the type
to plan his own escape.

393
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,030
Either Oh Jung Ran helped him,

394
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:39,070
or Park Hyun Jun and Chloe
broke him out.

395
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:43,070
We need to quickly find out
what Chloe is up to.

396
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:54,080
Wait.

397
00:26:55,220 --> 00:26:56,220
What's that?

398
00:26:58,490 --> 00:27:00,720
Did James drop this?

399
00:27:02,990 --> 00:27:03,990
Perfect.

400
00:27:04,530 --> 00:27:06,160
I could barely get a read on him,

401
00:27:06,630 --> 00:27:07,960
so let's go
through his wallet instead.

402
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:28,350
She told me to get out, so I did,
but she's in there alone.

403
00:27:29,850 --> 00:27:31,050
Will she be okay?

404
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:35,190
We're doing this to save my mom,
so please cooperate for now.

405
00:27:36,090 --> 00:27:38,730
All right.
What do you need me to tell you?

406
00:27:42,070 --> 00:27:44,800
When President Kim Myung Hui
first came to the Adele family,

407
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:47,170
please tell us
what it was like back then.

408
00:27:47,870 --> 00:27:49,870
I'm looking into Kim Dan Hui,

409
00:27:49,870 --> 00:27:51,610
and I need to know
what happened at the time.

410
00:27:53,010 --> 00:27:54,380
Are you talking...

411
00:27:55,110 --> 00:27:58,110
about the day
she showed up holding Park Min Jun?

412
00:28:01,250 --> 00:28:04,350
Gosh, just thinking about that day
makes my legs tremble.

413
00:28:06,490 --> 00:28:07,890
A dead person...

414
00:28:08,590 --> 00:28:11,590
showed up holding a baby.

415
00:28:13,130 --> 00:28:15,100
I'm telling you,
I thought she was a ghost.

416
00:28:16,230 --> 00:28:18,840
Wait, a dead person?

417
00:28:18,970 --> 00:28:20,040
That's right.

418
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:23,670
She was definitely dead.

419
00:28:29,010 --> 00:28:32,650
But she went to an OB-GYN clinic,
had a baby,

420
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:34,680
disappeared without a trace,

421
00:28:36,820 --> 00:28:38,250
and then suddenly reappeared.

422
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:43,930
She said she lost her memory
during childbirth,

423
00:28:44,260 --> 00:28:46,100
which is why she came back so late.

424
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,230
I guess...

425
00:28:48,870 --> 00:28:51,470
only she and that obstetrician...

426
00:28:51,470 --> 00:28:53,700
know the truth about what happened.

427
00:28:55,370 --> 00:28:56,610
That obstetrician.

428
00:28:57,170 --> 00:28:58,810
Could we try contacting the doctor?

429
00:28:59,180 --> 00:29:00,180
Gosh, no.

430
00:29:00,710 --> 00:29:03,450
He shut down his clinic
and left for the US.

431
00:29:04,450 --> 00:29:05,580
He'll be hard to find.

432
00:29:05,780 --> 00:29:06,850
Still,

433
00:29:06,850 --> 00:29:08,890
maybe you could give us the name
of the clinic or the doctor.

434
00:29:09,750 --> 00:29:10,950
It was Baek OB-GYN.

435
00:29:12,490 --> 00:29:14,620
The doctor's name was Baek Jun Gi.

436
00:29:18,730 --> 00:29:19,730
Baek Jun Gi?

437
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,070
The name sounds familiar,
doesn't it?

438
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:29,570
He has the same name
as Temi Bio's CEO.

439
00:29:30,210 --> 00:29:31,210
That's how I remember it.

440
00:29:34,510 --> 00:29:35,510
I see.

441
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:37,450
I think that covers everything.

442
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:41,350
Go ahead and help Mr. Song
find a place to stay.

443
00:29:41,580 --> 00:29:43,350
It's all right. I can cover it.

444
00:29:43,550 --> 00:29:45,960
I'm offering, so just take it.
You should head out now.

445
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:49,860
Once you've helped Mr. Song,
head home.

446
00:29:50,330 --> 00:29:51,760
You should check on your mother.

447
00:29:53,130 --> 00:29:54,130
You're right.

448
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:55,670
Good.

449
00:29:56,300 --> 00:29:59,740
- Well, I'll be on my way then.
- Yes, of course.

450
00:30:03,570 --> 00:30:04,570
Thank you.

451
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:13,020
Doctor Baek Jun Gi from Baek OB-GYN.

452
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:15,150
That's my dad.

453
00:30:16,690 --> 00:30:17,750
Could President Kim...

454
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:21,060
have some connection to my dad?

455
00:30:28,130 --> 00:30:30,870
(Hanbit High School
62nd Graduation Ceremony)

456
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:35,410
Why are they in the photo
with Dr. Baek?

457
00:30:37,070 --> 00:30:39,740
Don't tell me Chloe is...

458
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:42,610
She's Baek Jin Ju.

459
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,080
She was alive?

460
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:55,960
(Hanbit High School
62nd Graduation Ceremony)

461
00:30:56,660 --> 00:30:59,900
My father told me I was born
at his OB-GYN clinic.

462
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:04,730
Then does that mean Min Jun and I
were born on the same day...

463
00:31:05,370 --> 00:31:07,600
and at the same place?

464
00:31:09,810 --> 00:31:10,870
Come to think of it,

465
00:31:12,210 --> 00:31:13,980
after Dr. Baek came back to the US,

466
00:31:14,810 --> 00:31:16,150
he looked for someone.

467
00:31:16,910 --> 00:31:18,350
He said it was the person
who delivered you...

468
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:20,280
and that he wanted to help them.

469
00:31:21,850 --> 00:31:22,920
Don't tell me that person was...

470
00:31:28,220 --> 00:31:30,690
(President Kim Myung Hui)

471
00:31:33,660 --> 00:31:36,200
So Chloe was
Dr. Baek's daughter after all.

472
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:40,040
Baek Jin Ju was alive.

473
00:31:42,540 --> 00:31:43,640
Kim Dan Hui.

474
00:31:44,710 --> 00:31:47,410
She's the one who delivered me
at my dad's clinic?

475
00:31:48,980 --> 00:31:52,050
What exactly was her connection
to my dad?

476
00:32:57,410 --> 00:33:00,180
(Pearl in Red)

477
00:33:00,580 --> 00:33:03,820
How did Kim Dan Hui manage
to endure all those years?

478
00:33:04,020 --> 00:33:05,890
She had someone to protect.

479
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:08,260
Why does she care
so much about Min Jun,

480
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:11,360
yet she's determined
to remain married to Hyun Jun?

481
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:12,400
What's this?

482
00:33:12,460 --> 00:33:13,830
"Claim for Damages."

483
00:33:14,530 --> 00:33:16,570
One million dollars?

484
00:33:16,570 --> 00:33:18,330
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
